---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="food | human nature health"
  description="a simple guide to real food, energy, and nourishment."
>
  <section class="page-hero section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">food</p>
      <h1>food is not just fuel. it shapes how you feel.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        what you eat affects energy, mood, clarity, and long-term health. simple, real food
        patterns often work better than complicated diets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>why food matters</h2>
        <p>
          food gives your body the materials it needs to function. it affects blood sugar,
          hormones, brain function, and physical performance.
        </p>
        <p>
          when food is consistent and clean, the body usually responds with more stable
          energy and clearer thinking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>what goes wrong</h2>
        <p>
          processed foods, sugar spikes, inconsistent eating, and low-quality ingredients
          can lead to crashes, brain fog, and unstable energy.
        </p>
        <p>
          many people are not eating in a way that supports steady function throughout
          the day.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>core principles</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p>eat mostly whole, real foods</p>
          <p>prioritize protein and nutrient-dense meals</p>
          <p>avoid constant snacking and sugar spikes</p>
          <p>drink enough water</p>
          <p>build consistent eating patterns</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section accent-section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>simple eating structure</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>morning</h3>
        <p>
          start with something that stabilizes energy. protein + simple foods usually work
          better than sugar-heavy meals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>day</h3>
        <p>
          eat meals that support steady energy instead of spikes and crashes. keep things
          simple and repeatable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>night</h3>
        <p>
          avoid heavy, chaotic eating late. let the body wind down instead of staying
          stimulated.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>common mistakes</h2>
        <p>
          overcomplicating food is one of the biggest mistakes. most people benefit from
          simple, repeatable meals rather than constantly changing diets.
        </p>
        <p>
          another mistake is ignoring how food actually makes you feel. energy and clarity
          are strong signals of what is working.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <p>
          simple food done consistently is more powerful than perfect diets done rarely.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="y2k-panel feature-card">
        <div class="panel-heading-row">
          <p class="panel-kicker">baseline</p>
          <span class="panel-stamp">simple</span>
        </div>
        <h2>a simple daily food baseline</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p>2–3 consistent meals per day</p>
          <p>each meal built around protein</p>
          <p>mostly whole, minimally processed foods</p>
          <p>stable carbs instead of sugar spikes</p>
          <p>water as main drink</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="y2k-panel feature-card">
        <div class="panel-heading-row">
          <p class="panel-kicker">checklist</p>
          <span class="panel-stamp">food</span>
        </div>
        <h2>simple food checklist</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p>eat protein with each meal</p>
          <p>keep meals simple and repeatable</p>
          <p>limit ultra-processed foods</p>
          <p>avoid constant snacking</p>
          <p>drink water consistently</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="two-panel-grid">
        <a href="/nervous-system" class="y2k-panel feature-card">
          <p class="panel-kicker">previous</p>
          <h3>nervous system</h3>
          <p>return to calming the body and reducing stress.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/mental-clarity" class="y2k-panel feature-card">
          <p class="panel-kicker">next</p>
          <h3>mental clarity</h3>
          <p>continue into focus, attention, and clear thinking.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
